text: Rock Springs is an American city in the state of Wyoming. It is in Sweetwater County. The city has about 23,526 people. On September 2, 1885, a riot between the Chinese immigrant miners and white immigrant miners killed at least 26 people and it was caused because of racial tensions and labor dispute. ==References== ==Other websites== *Official City of Rock Springs website Category:Cities in Wyoming Category:1888 establishments in the United States Category:1880s establishments in Wyoming Territory
title: Rock Springs, Wyoming
